Veggie Pinto Beet Bean Burger
  --America's Test Kitchen

2/3 c bulgur (medium) rinsed
1/2 tsp salt
1 1/2 c boiling water
1 large beet grated
3/4 c walnuts
1/2 c fresh basil
2 garlic cloves, minced
15 oz can pinto beans, rinsed and drained
4 oz jar carrot baby food
1 tbsp whole grain mustard
1 1/2 c panko bread crumbs
6 tbsp vegetable oil + more as needed
1 1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper

Bring 1 1/2 c water and 1/2 tsp salt to boil in small saucepan. Off heat, stir in bulgur, cover, and let stand until tender, 15-20 min. Drain bulgur, spread onto rimmed baking sheet, and let cool slightly. Pulse beet, walnuts, basil, and garlic in food processor until finely chopped, ~12 pulses, scraping down sides as needed. Add beans, baby food, 2 tbsp water, mustard, 1 1/2 tsp salt, and 1/2 tso pepper and pulse until well combined, ~8 pulses. Transfer mixture to large bowl and stir in panko and bulgur. Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 200F. Divide mixture into 8 equal portions and pack into 3 1/2" wide patties. Heat 3 tbsl oil in 12" nonstick skillet over medium high heat until shimmering. Gently lay 4 patties in skillet and cook until crisp and well browned on first side, ~4 min. Gently flip and cook until crisp and well browned on second side, ~4 min, add more oil as needed. Transfer burgers to wire rack set in rimmed baking sheet and place in oven to keep warm. Wipe out skillet with paper towels and repeat with remaining patties. Serve on buns.

Sauce:
3/4 c vegan mayo
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp vegan worcestershire
1 tbsp brown sugar
1 garlic clove minced
1 tbsp fresh chives
3/4 tsp pepper

Whisk all ingredients together.
